	   <tr><td colspan=2>Am pretty happy with being a wizard and am surprised that so many think wizards are limitted in what they can do.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>    We have a great group snare and can kite as well as any druid.  After you have reached 200 Int ( 186 if you have an ench as a partner as I do)  You add AC and HP with some Agi thrown in for good measure.   At raids  you add all the MR you can to avoid getting feared and spend a fortune on peridots for manaskin.. but well worth it.  Once you have tanked up a bit ( I am ususally 2200hp on raids plus 580hp or so from manskin)  I find I can be added crowd control by proctecting the Ench and the Cleric ( Root and/or kill)  This allows the tanks to remain on the main target.  I dont run artound screaming  "On Me"   Upsets me to see a wizzy do that.  Root , step back, snare, kill.<br>If your channeling is so bad you always get interrupts you have a problem :)  Fix the problem<br>  I can quite happily stand toe to toe with a Rygorr Elite Guard and kill him while he smacks me.  Dont reccomend it but nice to know I can.<br>    With Jboots there is no better solo class and I often pull for the groups that I am with... rooting and snaring just before arrival.   AE spells are fantastic if used right.  Tears of Druzzil will do 1800 damage to a single mob -  Nice :)<br>    I do admit wizzys have a hard time at lower levels but I honestly think the main problem is too many bad wizards out there.<br>   It is a hard class to master but well worth the effort.  Now if only I could get people to stop calling me a porter.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
