	   <tr><td colspan=2>Evocation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Here are all the decisions you will have to make: first, if you are going to play your character past lvl 30'ish, go play another class, the wizard is the current broken class.  Second, if you like punishment, play a wizard.  Start off and buy all the spells you can at every level.  That AoE spell you think isn't worth a damn is really just good practice for when you learn to quad kite.  Put all your points into intelligence.  Then strength because it's a real pain in the ass to carry things around and get encumbered and such. Play a high elf a dark elf or a gnome.  No one else has infravision/uv and the beginning levels are a real pain without it.  Specialize in evocation, get as many runes and pages and other research crap as you can even if it isn't yours &lt;researching necro spells gives you the same skill advance as researching wizard spells&gt;.  Then, when you get to 29, sell your ports to make money.  Do this ruthlessly.  Also, learn to quad kite using bonds of force.  Keep quad kiting, do not group it isn't as fast.  Then, when you hit 40'ish, start grouping to make friends who will take pity on you at lvl 50+ and group with you then.  Do your soltemple quests.  They are good.  Good luck.<br>-Apollyon<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
