	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Create an Euridite wiz and put 25 pts into INT and 5 pts into AGI or DEX.&nbsp;&nbsp;Firstly, get on the boat and goto North Qeynos to power level to 3-4. Remember to bind yourself before picking a fight there else your in for another long boat ride.  Levels 5-6 go hunt the entrance area to Black Burrow in Qeynos Hills.  Collect gnolls teeth to turn-in to Captian Tillian in the Areana of South Qeynos and Rabid pelts to turn-in to a priestess in the Clerics Guide (Looks like a flying saucer). Both item quests provide great experience.  From 7-10 hunt inside Black Burrow on the main ground level across from the entrance to avoid the constant trains other low levels will pull to you if you hunt next to the zone boundary.  I can not stress this enough for casters who spend time meditating in Black Burrow (BB).  Once in a great while will a patrolling gnoll bother you and if he's to strong then run for the zone and you should still survive.  If you group alot goto Wisp Island ( first boat stop on trip from Qeynos to Euridin) to hunt wisps.  DO NOT MESS WITH THE KERRAN ANIMALS as they team up and usually will.  Hunt willow wisps ( must have a magic weapon to hit them plus the Light Stones and the Greater Light Stones can be turned in to a lady at the Gypsy camp for exp and money..... GLS give a book that sells for 8 pp) until level 14-15 and then hunt the Kerran Cat people with a small group or tank until level 17 ( Tolo and Holo are easy prey but they hit hard..... Great Experience) At lvl 17 I went to the windmill in Lake of Ill Omen and leveled in three hours with a group.  However the Scarecrows on Mills Farm in West Karana give great exp from 15-17 and there is plenty to hunt in North Karana and East Karana from level 16-20+.  <br><br>Good Luck and Good Journeys<br>Irrenki Level 18 wizzard on Tallon Zek<br><br>AKA Superspanky<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
